    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 4,
    "last_activity_date" : 1530122473,
    "creation_date" : 1530122473,
    "answer_id" : 51068901,
    "question_id" : 28291691,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I faced this issue deploying on Dokku, for some reason it was choosing JDK 1.7</p>\n\n<p>Creating a <code>system.properties</code> file and setting <code>java.runtime.version=1.8</code> solved the issue. Dokku now uses Java version 8.\n<a href=\"https://github.com/heroku/heroku-buildpack-java\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Choosing a JDK on Heroku</a> </p>\n\n<p>I Never had to do it before...</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1383947,
      "reputation" : 51,
      "user_id" : 1316369,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/662f06de090f443d9d97196e0d9b8565?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "user1316369",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1316369/user1316369"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1540236679,
    "last_edit_date" : 1540236679,
    "creation_date" : 1540229281,
    "answer_id" : 52934700,
    "question_id" : 28291691,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>On Windows machine you can temporarily set Java version.<br>\nFor example, to change the version to Java 8, run this command on <code>cmd</code>: </p>\n\n<pre><code>set JAVA_HOME=C:\\\\...\\jdk1.8.0_65\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
