    "question_id" : 28291691,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Using IntelliJ I just had to install another (higher) JDK Version. After restarting IDE, everything worked and even all dependencies were solved.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 2038913,
      "reputation" : 4619,
      "user_id" : 1820583,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 84,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/tF16j.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Eduardo Briguenti Vieira",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1820583/eduardo-briguenti-vieira"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1598629592,
    "creation_date" : 1598629592,
    "answer_id" : 63637042,
    "question_id" : 28291691,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>In my case (IntelliJ), I needed to check if I had <strong>the right Runner</strong> for maven:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Preferences</li>\n<li>Build, Execution, Deployment</li>\n<li>Maven -&gt; Runner</li>\n</ol>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/OHSxI.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/OHSxI.png\" alt=\"Preferences\" /></a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 15344798,
      "reputation" : 319,
      "user_id" : 12391466,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-de6a1HxypHg/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/ACevoQO1yZZec-rBsyPJ09fvTJVIhldLpg/mo/s256-rj/photo.jpg",
      "display_name" : "Jason Huang",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/12391466/jason-huang"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 3,
    "last_activity_date" : 1617653809,
    "last_edit_date" : 1617653809,
    "creation_date" : 1617638922,
    "answer_id" : 66955988,
    "question_id" : 28291691,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I have similar problem when I was trying to deploy my spring boot project to heroku, although my problem is <code>invalid target release: 11</code>.\nI solved it by adding a new file <code>system.properties</code> and the content added to the file is <code>java.runtime.version=11</code> (For me I am using JDK 11).</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 21727914,
      "reputation" : 1,
      "user_id" : 16037076,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgdTRhNcah7iS9pvoJLdXZR57TR0_AJhejbM5EOQg=k-s256",
      "display_name" : "Kyle ",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/16037076/kyle"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1623134739,
    "creation_date" : 1623134739,
    "answer_id" : 67882644,
    "question_id" : 28291691,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>NETBEANS\n<strong>Error</strong>:\nFailed to execute goal org.apache.maven.pluginsmaven-compiler-plugin3.1compile (default-compile) on project doit Fatal error compiling invalid target release 11 - [Help 1]</p>\n<p><strong>How I solved my problem:</strong>\n.Right click on the project.\n.Go to Properties.\n.Click on Source.\n.Go to Source/Binary Format and change to the latest version</p>\n<p>In my case (1.8)</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 7996752,
      "reputation" : 61,
      "user_id" : 6032797,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/14W4A.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Hieu Nguyen",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/6032797/hieu-nguyen"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1624807667,
    "creation_date" : 1624807667,
    "answer_id" : 68152640,
    "question_id" : 28291691,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>First, if you are using eclipse, please check Build Path -&gt; Configure Build Path -&gt; Java Build Path, see which java version your project is using. I recommend using Java 1.8.\nSecond, check the pom.xml file. ctrl + F to search the text &quot;java.version&quot; =&gt; change it to 1.8.\nThird install Java 1.8 and then change your JAVE_HOME path to point to Java 1.8 folder.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 26206668,
      "reputation" : 261,
      "user_id" : 19886178,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/U93WP.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Vishal Bramhankar",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/19886178/vishal-bramhankar"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1665844130,
    "creation_date" : 1665844130,
    "answer_id" : 74080312,
    "question_id" : 28291691,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Verify your jdk version in your pom.xml and environmental variables are same or not. if not make it same.</p>\n<p>At pom.xml -&gt;</p>\n<pre><code>&lt;properties&gt;\n        &lt;java.version&gt;11&lt;/java.version&gt;\n&lt;/properties&gt;\n</code></pre>\n<p>At environmental variables -&gt;\nJAVA_HOME = C:\\Program Files\\Java\\jdk-11.0.13</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 2800537,
      "reputation" : 506,
      "user_id" : 2408863,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/fc594b0407c6c9357a7d04ef6530ca0d?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "tonnoz",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2408863/tonnoz"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1676986517,
    "creation_date" : 1676986517,
    "answer_id" : 75521252,
    "question_id" : 28291691,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>In my case bumping the version of the <code>maven-compiler-plugin</code> from <code>3.8.1</code> to <code>3.10.1</code> solved the issue:</p>\n<pre><code>&lt;plugin&gt;\n   &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-compiler-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;\n   &lt;version&gt;3.10.1&lt;/version&gt;\n   &lt;configuration&gt;\n   &lt;release&gt;${maven.compiler.release}&lt;/release&gt;\n   &lt;/configuration&gt;\n&lt;/plugin&gt;\n</code></pre>\n<p>where <code>${maven.compiler.release}</code> = your java version</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 2985164,
      "reputation" : 6351,
      "user_id" : 2534191,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 25,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/lGNk40l9.png?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Yuriy N.",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2534191/yuriy-n"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1742191360,
    "last_edit_date" : 1742191360,
    "creation_date" : 1693484085,
    "answer_id" : 77015737,
    "question_id" : 28291691,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I had a similar failure when I tried to build a Maven project in Netbeans.\nMy pom file looks like this:</p>\n<pre><code>        &lt;properties&gt;\n            &lt;project.build.sourceEncoding&gt;UTF-8&lt;/project.build.sourceEncoding&gt;\n            &lt;maven.compiler.source&gt;17&lt;/maven.compiler.source&gt;\n            &lt;maven.compiler.target&gt;17&lt;/maven.compiler.target&gt;\n            &lt;exec.mainClass&gt;com.example.Main&lt;/exec.mainClass&gt;\n        &lt;/properties&gt;\n        &lt;build&gt;\n            &lt;sourceDirectory&gt;src&lt;/sourceDirectory&gt;\n            &lt;plugins&gt;\n            &lt;plugin&gt;\n                &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-compiler-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;\n                &lt;version&gt;3.7.0&lt;/version&gt;\n                &lt;configuration&gt;\n                &lt;source&gt;17&lt;/source&gt;\n                &lt;target&gt;17&lt;/target&gt;\n                    &lt;encoding&gt;${project.build.sourceEncoding}&lt;/encoding&gt;\n                &lt;/configuration&gt;\n            &lt;/plugin&gt; \n            ...\n</code></pre>\n<p>But Java platform for the project was set to 1.8 (as it is the default Java platform in my Netbeans configuration).</p>\n<p>Solution: <code>Right-click on project Properties-&gt;Build-&gt;Compile-&gt;Java Platform-&gt; choose JDK 17 from dropdown. </code></p>\n<p>If the dropdown does not have the required Java platform, it should be downloaded, installed, and then configured thru <code>Tools-&gt;Java platforms</code>.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 4195407,
      "reputation" : 467,
      "user_id" : 3436941,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 75,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ac250f9439c4a4c917cb1d3b106a844b?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "Khasan 24-7",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3436941/khasan-24-7"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1741238763,
    "creation_date" : 1741238763,
    "answer_id" : 79488349,
    "question_id" : 28291691,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I also faced the same problem, maven is giving an error saying invalid target release. After an hour of investigation, I have found out that in my Jenkins file wrong version of jdk was shown, and, i have recently upgraded version of jdk and forgot to change in Jenkinsfile. After changing it everything started working as expected.</p>\n"
  } ],
